WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.655 --> 00:00:25.058
[thunder rumbles softly]

2
00:01:09.069 --> 00:01:12.305
[car engine revving]

3
00:01:17.377 --> 00:01:20.379
[song on car radio]
♪ All day long I'm racin'

4
00:01:20.380 --> 00:01:22.681
♪ Get up to the floor

5
00:01:22.682 --> 00:01:25.685
[chilling music]

6
00:01:31.658 --> 00:01:33.859
-[car engine revving]
-♪ Get me out

7
00:01:33.860 --> 00:01:37.262
♪ Think I've lost control

8
00:01:37.263 --> 00:01:39.299
♪ Get me out

9
00:01:40.967 --> 00:01:42.968
[car engine revving]

10
00:01:42.969 --> 00:01:46.872
[loud music on car radio]

11
00:01:46.873 --> 00:01:50.476
♪ Get it out get it out
Get it out come on ♪

12
00:01:50.477 --> 00:01:51.877
[♪]

13
00:01:51.878 --> 00:01:57.082
♪ I gotta run back run
back Around the sun ♪

14
00:01:57.083 --> 00:01:58.884
[car engine revving]

15
00:01:58.885 --> 00:02:03.689
♪ Get it out get it out
Before I lose my mind ♪

16
00:02:03.690 --> 00:02:05.258
[loud thump]

17
00:02:06.159 --> 00:02:08.795
[truck horn blaring]

18
00:02:11.364 --> 00:02:13.466
[car tires screeching]

19
00:02:14.734 --> 00:02:16.368
♪ ...I'm runnin'

20
00:02:16.369 --> 00:02:19.572
-[James panting]
-♪ Runnin' from my past

21
00:02:21.374 --> 00:02:23.375
[Mary] Oh. come on.

22
00:02:23.376 --> 00:02:25.377
-[running footsteps]
-[Mary panting]

23
00:02:25.378 --> 00:02:27.679
You've got to be kidding me.

24
00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:29.081
- ♪ Get me out

25
00:02:29.082 --> 00:02:30.282
[car door opens]

26
00:02:30.283 --> 00:02:32.017
[music stops]

27
00:02:32.018 --> 00:02:34.153
- I am so sorry. I...

28
00:02:34.154 --> 00:02:35.921
Are you okay?

29
00:02:35.922 --> 00:02:37.422
- Yeah.
No. I'm fine. I'm fine.

30
00:02:37.423 --> 00:02:39.658
- Here. let me help you.

31
00:02:39.659 --> 00:02:42.662
- [both panting]

32
00:02:43.630 --> 00:02:44.664
- Uh...

33
00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:48.834
Sorry about all this.

34
00:02:48.835 --> 00:02:50.068
[bus honking]

35
00:02:50.069 --> 00:02:51.470
-[Mary] Sure. okay.
-[James] I got it.

36
00:02:51.471 --> 00:02:52.839
- The latch is broken.

37
00:02:54.073 --> 00:02:55.541
[grunts]
Shoot. that's my bus.

38
00:02:55.542 --> 00:02:59.712
Hey. Hey. hey! Wait!

39
00:03:02.148 --> 00:03:05.984
- Hang on. I got it.
[groans] Oh. fuck.

40
00:03:05.985 --> 00:03:08.020
[bus honking]

41
00:03:08.021 --> 00:03:10.355
- You can just...
Sorry.

42
00:03:10.356 --> 00:03:12.157
[bus door closes]

43
00:03:12.158 --> 00:03:13.692
- [groans]

44
00:03:13.693 --> 00:03:16.729
[bus departing]

45
00:03:18.765 --> 00:03:21.300
[James] Well. I'm officially
an asshole.

46
00:03:21.301 --> 00:03:22.801
Where were you heading?

47
00:03:22.802 --> 00:03:24.169
[Mary] The city.

48
00:03:24.170 --> 00:03:26.171
Where were you going?

49
00:03:26.172 --> 00:03:27.740
- Just up the pass.

50
00:03:29.175 --> 00:03:31.977
- I guess it wasn't meant to be.

51
00:03:31.978 --> 00:03:34.580
- So what are you gonna do?

52
00:03:34.581 --> 00:03:36.583
- Can just head back
into town. I guess.

53
00:03:43.556 --> 00:03:45.290
[James] What's it called?

54
00:03:45.291 --> 00:03:47.593
[Mary] Silent Hill.

55
00:03:47.594 --> 00:03:49.462
There's a trail down that way.

56
00:03:50.797 --> 00:03:51.597
- Cool.

57
00:03:51.598 --> 00:03:53.733
What's that down there
on the water?

58
00:03:56.402 --> 00:03:59.037
- That's the Lakeview.

59
00:03:59.038 --> 00:04:00.772
It's a hotel.

60
00:04:00.773 --> 00:04:04.209
The view of the lake
from the rooftop is so pretty.

61
00:04:04.210 --> 00:04:07.179
- Pretty enough
they named a hotel after it?

62
00:04:07.180 --> 00:04:08.280
- You nearly run me down.

63
00:04:08.281 --> 00:04:11.116
and now you're giving me
a hard time?

64
00:04:11.117 --> 00:04:12.719
- Yeah. shit. Sorry. Um...

65
00:04:13.953 --> 00:04:14.953
- [chuckles]

66
00:04:14.954 --> 00:04:16.388
- I deserved that. didn't I?

67
00:04:16.389 --> 00:04:19.691
Mm. I'm James. by the way.

68
00:04:19.692 --> 00:04:20.592
- Mary.

69
00:04:20.593 --> 00:04:22.894
- Well. like. seriously. Mary.
let me drive you home.

70
00:04:22.895 --> 00:04:25.397
I can save you
a sprained ankle or two.

71
00:04:25.398 --> 00:04:27.966
- I don't even know you. James.

72
00:04:27.967 --> 00:04:30.569
- All right. Well. I'm just
gonna have to stand here.

73
00:04:30.570 --> 00:04:33.071
watch you go down.
make sure you don't fall.

74
00:04:33.072 --> 00:04:34.273
- Seems like appropriate penance

75
00:04:34.274 --> 00:04:36.174
for screwing up my day.

76
00:04:36.175 --> 00:04:37.409
[birds chirping]

77
00:04:37.410 --> 00:04:38.778
- [sniffles]

78
00:04:45.118 --> 00:04:47.387
- So. are you coming or what?

79
00:04:55.995 --> 00:04:58.831
[suitcases thudding]

80
00:05:01.267 --> 00:05:02.502
[hood shuts]

81
00:05:05.104 --> 00:05:07.673
[wind whooshing]

82
00:05:07.674 --> 00:05:10.877
[ominous burst of music]

83
00:05:25.692 --> 00:05:27.794
- Silent Hill summer storm.

84
00:05:28.928 --> 00:05:31.196
Doesn't happen often.

85
00:05:31.197 --> 00:05:32.932
But when it does...

86
00:05:38.004 --> 00:05:39.971
- [gasps sharply]

87
00:05:39.972 --> 00:05:43.009
[club music playing]

88
00:05:43.976 --> 00:05:47.013
[phone vibrating]

89
00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:49.349
[sniffles]

90
00:05:59.025 --> 00:06:00.760
[beer mug clanks]

91
00:06:01.594 --> 00:06:03.529
- Think it's time to go.

92
00:06:04.597 --> 00:06:07.933
- All right. All right.

93
00:06:07.934 --> 00:06:09.067
[James groans]

94
00:06:09.068 --> 00:06:10.135
-Jesus!
-[glass shatters]

95
00:06:10.136 --> 00:06:11.436
[James] Sorry.

96
00:06:11.437 --> 00:06:12.537
Sorry. That's on me.

97
00:06:12.538 --> 00:06:14.940
[Bouncer] Let's go. asshole.

98
00:06:14.941 --> 00:06:16.441
[grunts and groans]

99
00:06:16.442 --> 00:06:17.909
[furniture clattering]

100
00:06:17.910 --> 00:06:20.880
[phone vibrating]

101
00:06:24.617 --> 00:06:26.853
-[Man] Get outta here.
-[Bouncer] Let's go. Let's go.

102
00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:28.921
[James] Yeah? Come on!

103
00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:32.190
Come on!

104
00:06:32.191 --> 00:06:34.326
Yo. get the fuck off me!

105
00:06:34.327 --> 00:06:36.763
Let go of me! [grunts]

106
00:06:38.131 --> 00:06:40.599
Fuck you! Fuck you!

107
00:06:40.600 --> 00:06:41.901
[men grunt with effort]

108
00:06:43.403 --> 00:06:45.203
[Bouncer] Nighty night. fucker.

109
00:06:45.204 --> 00:06:47.539
[rock music playing]

110
00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:49.642
[door slams]

111
00:06:50.610 --> 00:06:53.880
[phone vibrating]

112
00:06:59.018 --> 00:07:00.519
[James groans]

113
00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:02.320
[M] [over phone]
There you are.

114
00:07:02.321 --> 00:07:04.823
How are you?

115
00:07:04.824 --> 00:07:07.192
[James] [over phone]
Not so great.

116
00:07:07.193 --> 00:07:08.694
[M] You've been drinking.

117
00:07:10.663 --> 00:07:13.532
It felt like we were moving
in the right direction. James.

118
00:07:13.533 --> 00:07:15.333
- I know. [groans]

119
00:07:15.334 --> 00:07:17.636
[M] [over phone] You've got
to stop beating yourself up.

120
00:07:17.637 --> 00:07:19.171
[James sighs]

121
00:07:19.172 --> 00:07:20.739
- Here's what I need you to do.

122
00:07:20.740 --> 00:07:23.642
Get home. drink some water.
get some sleep.

123
00:07:23.643 --> 00:07:26.612
Reset and come
to our appointment tomorrow.

124
00:07:27.346 --> 00:07:31.918
- Yeah. tomorrow.
Yeah. Okay.

125
00:07:33.219 --> 00:07:34.787
We'll see.

126
00:07:36.022 --> 00:07:38.223
[claps of thunder]

127
00:07:38.224 --> 00:07:41.461
[heavy downpour of rain]

128
00:07:46.332 --> 00:07:47.767
[lock clicks. door opens]

129
00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:52.538
[door slams shut]

130
00:07:55.208 --> 00:07:56.209
[keys thud]

131
00:07:57.643 --> 00:07:59.644
[James sighs deeply]

132
00:07:59.645 --> 00:08:03.883
[rain pattering]

133
00:08:06.219 --> 00:08:09.222
[disturbing music playing]

134
00:08:16.863 --> 00:08:20.066
[sharp gasp. groaning in pain]

135
00:08:26.038 --> 00:08:27.706
Oh. God.

136
00:08:27.707 --> 00:08:29.775
[bottle thuds. rolling]

137
00:08:35.848 --> 00:08:39.051
[unsettling music playing]

138
00:08:54.867 --> 00:08:58.070
[mellow music playing]

139
00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:05.545
[thunder rumbles]

140
00:09:06.812 --> 00:09:09.881
[Mary] James.
so much time has passed.

141
00:09:09.882 --> 00:09:11.550
-[keys jingling]
-I know that.

142
00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:13.018
But I'm asking...

143
00:09:13.019 --> 00:09:15.922
I'm begging you
to please come back.

144
00:09:17.256 --> 00:09:18.925
To our place.

145
00:09:20.259 --> 00:09:21.961
Something's happened.

146
00:09:22.862 --> 00:09:26.198
Please. James. I need you.

147
00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:31.137
Love. Mary.

148
00:09:46.352 --> 00:09:49.589
[rain pattering]

149
00:09:50.856 --> 00:09:54.060
[car engine revs]

150
00:10:03.769 --> 00:10:04.971
[car engine stops]

151
00:10:11.877 --> 00:10:13.445
[loud clap of thunder]

152
00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:15.580
-Jesus.
-[car door shuts]

153
00:10:15.581 --> 00:10:18.818
[rain pattering on car roof]

154
00:10:27.660 --> 00:10:28.928
[James] [voice-over]
It's her.

155
00:10:33.265 --> 00:10:35.368
It's always been her.

156
00:10:38.371 --> 00:10:39.805
Mary.

157
00:10:43.476 --> 00:10:45.244
The girl of my dreams.

158
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:48.681
The love of my life.

159
00:10:55.488 --> 00:10:58.691
[coughing]

160
00:11:03.529 --> 00:11:05.765
[breathing heavily]

161
00:11:09.502 --> 00:11:10.736
[car door opens]

162
00:11:17.343 --> 00:11:18.344
[car door closes]

163
00:11:19.345 --> 00:11:22.348
[crunching footsteps]

164
00:11:27.286 --> 00:11:29.388
[door creaks open]

165
00:11:40.366 --> 00:11:43.369
[faucets clatter]

166
00:11:50.776 --> 00:11:53.979
[pensive music playing]

167
00:12:08.761 --> 00:12:10.396
[James] [voice-over]
Our place.

168
00:12:17.703 --> 00:12:19.105
Our town.

169
00:12:21.373 --> 00:12:22.374
[car beeps]

170
00:12:24.810 --> 00:12:26.345
Our love.

171
00:12:31.217 --> 00:12:32.485
It was here.

172
00:12:37.990 --> 00:12:40.192
It was everywhere.

173
00:12:42.361 --> 00:12:45.364
[uneasy music playing]

174
00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:51.237
And now. they keep telling me
to let go.

175
00:12:54.807 --> 00:12:56.242
To move on.

176
00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:05.117
But how can I ever do that?

177
00:13:10.022 --> 00:13:12.358
When you're calling me?

178
00:13:43.389 --> 00:13:46.392
[rustling]

179
00:13:53.432 --> 00:13:54.500
Hello?

180
00:13:57.536 --> 00:13:58.903
- Grab a bag.

181
00:13:58.904 --> 00:14:00.206
- What?

182
00:14:06.111 --> 00:14:08.413
[Angela] Careful.

183
00:14:08.414 --> 00:14:09.582
They're heavy.

184
00:14:11.784 --> 00:14:14.419
- So. where's all this
coming from?

185
00:14:14.420 --> 00:14:16.421
[Angela] This?

186
00:14:16.422 --> 00:14:18.489
You mean the ashes?

187
00:14:18.490 --> 00:14:20.358
[James] Yeah.

188
00:14:20.359 --> 00:14:23.828
[Angela] It started with
the fires in the summer.

189
00:14:23.829 --> 00:14:25.598
[panting]
Tore through the forests.

190
00:14:27.499 --> 00:14:30.034
Some are still burning.

191
00:14:30.035 --> 00:14:32.837
And then came the rains.

192
00:14:32.838 --> 00:14:34.939
- Right.

193
00:14:34.940 --> 00:14:37.408
So. there's someone...

194
00:14:37.409 --> 00:14:40.212
someone I care about.
and I need to find her.

195
00:14:41.714 --> 00:14:43.115
- [panting] You won't.

196
00:14:44.350 --> 00:14:47.352
Floods overran
the water treatment plant.

197
00:14:47.353 --> 00:14:48.820
When water gets contaminated.

198
00:14:48.821 --> 00:14:51.322
people don't stick around.

199
00:14:51.323 --> 00:14:53.524
- Look. I'm still going to try
and head into town

200
00:14:53.525 --> 00:14:54.994
if you could just...

201
00:14:59.398 --> 00:15:00.832
Well...

202
00:15:00.833 --> 00:15:02.634
thanks. anyway.

203
00:15:02.635 --> 00:15:03.903
- Wait.

204
00:15:04.937 --> 00:15:07.906
You don't find
who you're looking for.

205
00:15:07.907 --> 00:15:11.342
you can always
come back and find me.

206
00:15:11.343 --> 00:15:12.411
I'm Angela.

207
00:15:13.412 --> 00:15:14.712
- Angela.

208
00:15:14.713 --> 00:15:16.048
Sure.

209
00:15:35.100 --> 00:15:38.370
[soft dramatic music playing]

210
00:15:39.738 --> 00:15:40.905
[Mary sighs]

211
00:15:40.906 --> 00:15:44.409
[James] So. what if I...

212
00:15:44.410 --> 00:15:45.544
moved here?

213
00:15:47.146 --> 00:15:50.048
- No museums. No clubs.

214
00:15:50.049 --> 00:15:51.549
Zero anonymity.

215
00:15:51.550 --> 00:15:54.953
- Yeah. I'm just
as shocked as you are.

216
00:15:54.954 --> 00:15:56.654
- You'd really
want to move here?

217
00:15:56.655 --> 00:15:58.323
- I would.

218
00:15:58.324 --> 00:15:59.257
- Why?

219
00:15:59.258 --> 00:16:02.226
- Well. there's this girl.

220
00:16:02.227 --> 00:16:06.097
And she's not much
to look at. but.

221
00:16:06.098 --> 00:16:07.366
[kissing]

222
00:16:09.568 --> 00:16:10.601
What?

223
00:16:10.602 --> 00:16:13.104
You don't think we're ready
to live together?

224
00:16:13.105 --> 00:16:15.541
- There are parts of me
you haven't seen.

225
00:16:16.742 --> 00:16:18.544
What if who I am scares you?

226
00:16:19.712 --> 00:16:21.046
- It won't.

227
00:16:22.014 --> 00:16:23.716
I promise you.

228
00:16:28.387 --> 00:16:30.055
[kissing]

229
00:16:34.026 --> 00:16:35.360
Hey. Hey. hey. hey.

230
00:16:35.361 --> 00:16:36.961
Hey now. now tilt
your head back.

231
00:16:36.962 --> 00:16:38.563
[Mary groans]

232
00:16:38.564 --> 00:16:40.231
[both laughing]

233
00:16:40.232 --> 00:16:41.265
[Mary]
I can't believe this.

234
00:16:41.266 --> 00:16:43.334
[James] It's okay. I got you.

235
00:16:43.335 --> 00:16:47.138
I'm here.
I'll always be here.

236
00:16:47.139 --> 00:16:49.441
I mean it.

237
00:16:56.215 --> 00:16:59.418
[disturbing rhythmic drumbeats]

238
00:17:17.770 --> 00:17:21.040
[ominous music playing]

239
00:17:54.273 --> 00:17:56.175
[glass squeaks]

240
00:18:03.882 --> 00:18:05.084
I don't understand.

241
00:18:06.752 --> 00:18:09.788
[flies buzzing]

242
00:18:17.863 --> 00:18:21.100
[panting]

243
00:18:23.068 --> 00:18:24.403
[whispers] This is insane.

244
00:18:26.872 --> 00:18:30.109
[running footsteps]

245
00:18:31.777 --> 00:18:34.813
[breathing heavily]

246
00:18:46.258 --> 00:18:47.626
[shouts] Hello?!

247
00:18:49.761 --> 00:18:51.863
Can anyone hear me?

248
00:18:51.864 --> 00:18:54.399
[music heard in the distance]

249
00:18:58.270 --> 00:18:59.871
Is someone there?

250
00:18:59.872 --> 00:19:01.973
[music on speaker]

251
00:19:01.974 --> 00:19:04.075
Hello?

252
00:19:04.076 --> 00:19:07.312
[solemn music
playing on speaker]

253
00:19:25.264 --> 00:19:28.433
[faint music playing]

254
00:19:29.234 --> 00:19:32.437
[running footsteps]

255
00:19:34.239 --> 00:19:37.442
[music gets louder]

256
00:19:47.252 --> 00:19:50.455
[man snoring]

257
00:19:58.864 --> 00:19:59.898
Hello?

258
00:20:02.901 --> 00:20:04.503
Can you hear me?

259
00:20:09.007 --> 00:20:10.576
[metal clanks]

260
00:20:12.377 --> 00:20:15.581
[static on radio]

261
00:20:23.655 --> 00:20:26.290
-[James gasps]
-They're coming back.

262
00:20:26.291 --> 00:20:28.693
-Who?
-You know they're coming back.

263
00:20:28.694 --> 00:20:31.462
All that darkness.
you can't keep it away.

264
00:20:31.463 --> 00:20:33.798
- Just-just-just
get off me. all right?

265
00:20:33.799 --> 00:20:35.234
[panting in fear]

266
00:20:38.403 --> 00:20:41.607
[phone vibrating]

267
00:20:44.309 --> 00:20:47.078
- I wasn't expecting
a no-show. James.

268
00:20:47.079 --> 00:20:48.479
- I'm in Silent Hill.

269
00:20:48.480 --> 00:20:49.614
[M] [over phone] What?

270
00:20:49.615 --> 00:20:51.415
- I did... something's
happened here.

271
00:20:51.416 --> 00:20:53.384
Something really. really bad.

272
00:20:53.385 --> 00:20:54.452
[M] James.

273
00:20:54.453 --> 00:20:56.153
Listen to me carefully.

274
00:20:56.154 --> 00:20:58.089
This is getting out of control.

275
00:20:58.090 --> 00:20:59.690
[James] I need to go home...

276
00:20:59.691 --> 00:21:01.192
to Mary.

277
00:21:01.193 --> 00:21:02.893
[M] What did you say?

278
00:21:02.894 --> 00:21:04.362
I need you to come back.

279
00:21:04.363 --> 00:21:06.264
There's no home
for you there anymore.

280
00:21:06.265 --> 00:21:07.898
[signage buzzing]

281
00:21:07.899 --> 00:21:09.434
[M] James?

282
00:21:11.270 --> 00:21:12.270
James?

283
00:21:12.271 --> 00:21:13.605
- [groaning]

284
00:21:15.107 --> 00:21:18.343
[crunching footsteps]

285
00:21:19.111 --> 00:21:22.347
[signage buzzing]

286
00:21:31.123 --> 00:21:34.326
- [groaning]

287
00:21:36.395 --> 00:21:39.598
[static noise from radio]

288
00:21:42.267 --> 00:21:43.835
[creature screeches]

289
00:21:59.084 --> 00:22:02.454
[club music playing on speaker]

290
00:22:04.990 --> 00:22:06.223
[Mary] Everyone...

291
00:22:06.224 --> 00:22:07.224
this is James.

292
00:22:07.225 --> 00:22:08.025
- Hi.

293
00:22:08.026 --> 00:22:10.227
[Claudette] So Mary tells me
you're an artist.

294
00:22:10.228 --> 00:22:11.696
[James] Yeah. Painter.

295
00:22:11.697 --> 00:22:14.433
[Claudette] And you have
the perfect muse.

296
00:22:15.801 --> 00:22:18.602
- Our Mary.
she's something special.

297
00:22:18.603 --> 00:22:21.706
- Sparkling little apple
of her father's eye.

298
00:22:21.707 --> 00:22:23.808
- Oh. so you all know him. or...?

299
00:22:23.809 --> 00:22:24.975
- [chuckling]

300
00:22:24.976 --> 00:22:26.177
- Know him?

301
00:22:26.178 --> 00:22:28.079
Joshua Crane.

302
00:22:28.080 --> 00:22:30.881
Doesn't quite do it justice
when you say it out loud.

303
00:22:30.882 --> 00:22:32.516
- [in unison]
He changed our lives.

304
00:22:32.517 --> 00:22:34.118
- Mary's family.

305
00:22:34.119 --> 00:22:35.419
they built this town.

306
00:22:35.420 --> 00:22:36.921
Gave us purpose.

307
00:22:36.922 --> 00:22:41.025
- My life was spinning out
in all directions.

308
00:22:41.026 --> 00:22:43.928
Helped me put my head
back on straight.

309
00:22:43.929 --> 00:22:46.664
- I think we all
have a similar story.

310
00:22:46.665 --> 00:22:47.531
Mm.

311
00:22:47.532 --> 00:22:51.535
- We have a way of seeing things
here in Silent Hill.

312
00:22:51.536 --> 00:22:53.437
But don't worry.

313
00:22:53.438 --> 00:22:55.807
- I'm sure
we'll find a place for you.

314
00:23:00.078 --> 00:23:01.613
- [screams outside]

315
00:23:04.316 --> 00:23:05.751
[footsteps]

316
00:23:07.319 --> 00:23:08.620
- What is that?

317
00:23:09.521 --> 00:23:11.390
[flesh melting]

318
00:23:20.132 --> 00:23:23.402
[radio crackling]

319
00:23:26.872 --> 00:23:28.473
Who is that?!

320
00:23:31.042 --> 00:23:34.045
[sinister music playing]

321
00:23:36.148 --> 00:23:37.616
[creature shrieks]

322
00:23:41.319 --> 00:23:42.420
- [straining effort]

323
00:23:42.421 --> 00:23:45.023
[creature screeches]

324
00:23:50.962 --> 00:23:53.731
[trembling breath]

325
00:23:53.732 --> 00:23:56.967
[tense music playing]

326
00:23:56.968 --> 00:23:58.637
[metallic clatter]

327
00:24:03.742 --> 00:24:05.944
[breathing heavily]

328
00:24:07.746 --> 00:24:08.746
[static from radio]

329
00:24:08.747 --> 00:24:12.049
[Man] This is the Silent Hill
Emergency Operations System.

330
00:24:12.050 --> 00:24:14.452
This is not a test.

331
00:24:14.453 --> 00:24:16.720
City officials have issued
a health emergency

332
00:24:16.721 --> 00:24:19.356
for the city of Silent Hill
and surrounding areas.

333
00:24:19.357 --> 00:24:20.591
Residents are being ordered

334
00:24:20.592 --> 00:24:23.161
to evacuate this
area immediately.

335
00:24:25.230 --> 00:24:27.932
I repeat. this is not a test.

336
00:24:27.933 --> 00:24:30.000
What you are hearing
is not a test.

337
00:24:30.001 --> 00:24:32.136
This is the emergency
alert system.

338
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:35.973
Civil authorities are issuing...
-[emergency alert blaring]

339
00:24:35.974 --> 00:24:38.944
[wings flapping]

340
00:24:48.653 --> 00:24:51.890
[ground cracking]

341
00:25:20.085 --> 00:25:22.053
[creature screeches]

342
00:25:42.440 --> 00:25:44.643
[footsteps clanging]

343
00:25:46.444 --> 00:25:47.913
[James groans in pain]

344
00:25:51.249 --> 00:25:52.751
[rats squeaking]

345
00:25:55.754 --> 00:25:58.957
[James grunts with effort]

346
00:26:00.458 --> 00:26:03.662
[rats squeaking]

347
00:26:11.169 --> 00:26:12.203
[pipe clanging]

348
00:26:14.573 --> 00:26:16.808
[squelching]

349
00:26:20.345 --> 00:26:22.681
[insects chittering]

350
00:26:28.353 --> 00:26:31.656
[footsteps clanging]

351
00:26:41.766 --> 00:26:44.970
[eerie shrieking]

352
00:26:49.207 --> 00:26:52.210
[tense music playing]

353
00:27:07.158 --> 00:27:09.194
[James grunts]

354
00:27:19.571 --> 00:27:22.807
[straining]

355
00:27:32.484 --> 00:27:35.687
[insects chittering]

356
00:27:40.792 --> 00:27:42.327
[James grunts]

357
00:27:43.662 --> 00:27:45.864
[insects chittering]

358
00:27:48.767 --> 00:27:49.968
[yells in pain]

359
00:27:54.372 --> 00:27:55.773
[panting]

360
00:27:55.774 --> 00:27:58.977
[insects bustling]

361
00:28:06.985 --> 00:28:10.221
[soft tense music playing]

362
00:28:28.406 --> 00:28:29.908
[eerie squeal]

363
00:28:31.776 --> 00:28:33.712
[Mary] [whispers] James.

364
00:28:36.681 --> 00:28:38.216
- Mary?

365
00:28:40.251 --> 00:28:42.320
[soft. suspenseful
music playing]

366
00:28:46.791 --> 00:28:48.992
- Hello. handsome.

367
00:28:48.993 --> 00:28:51.361
How many times you get lost
this time around?

368
00:28:51.362 --> 00:28:53.397
- I just can't believe
how much stuff I had.

369
00:28:53.398 --> 00:28:54.598
- Come on. one last push.

370
00:28:54.599 --> 00:28:55.834
- Um-hmm.

371
00:28:56.601 --> 00:28:57.836
[kissing]

372
00:28:59.437 --> 00:29:00.671
- Let me help you with this.

373
00:29:00.672 --> 00:29:01.905
- Ooh. why thank you.

374
00:29:01.906 --> 00:29:03.842
[Mary] [chuckles softly]
You're so welcome.

375
00:29:06.711 --> 00:29:09.713
[tense music]

376
00:29:09.714 --> 00:29:12.917
[footsteps approaching]

377
00:29:38.009 --> 00:29:39.878
[door hinges squeak]

378
00:29:49.387 --> 00:29:52.357
[white noise from TV]

379
00:30:16.014 --> 00:30:19.250
[grunting in pain]

380
00:30:34.499 --> 00:30:35.500
[phone ringing]

381
00:30:36.501 --> 00:30:38.802
[James panting over phone]

382
00:30:38.803 --> 00:30:40.004
- Where are you?

383
00:30:41.739 --> 00:30:43.507
- [groaning] It hurts so bad.
I can't...

384
00:30:43.508 --> 00:30:45.309
I can't make it stop.

385
00:30:45.310 --> 00:30:48.011
- It's gonna be okay.
Just tell me where you are.

386
00:30:48.012 --> 00:30:49.813
[James] No. No.

387
00:30:49.814 --> 00:30:51.415
No. I can feel her.

388
00:30:51.416 --> 00:30:53.017
She's close.

389
00:30:53.818 --> 00:30:55.419
I think she's...

390
00:30:55.420 --> 00:30:58.423
- James? James?

391
00:30:59.424 --> 00:31:01.925
- [panting]

392
00:31:01.926 --> 00:31:03.361
[groaning]

393
00:31:08.633 --> 00:31:12.537
[heavy downpour]

394
00:31:20.812 --> 00:31:23.248
[thunder roaring]

395
00:31:24.415 --> 00:31:27.952
[rain pattering]

396
00:31:33.424 --> 00:31:34.524
[voicemail]
The mailbox is full

397
00:31:34.525 --> 00:31:36.793
and cannot accept
any messages at this time.

398
00:31:36.794 --> 00:31:38.829
Goodbye.

399
00:31:38.830 --> 00:31:40.031
[phone thuds]

400
00:31:43.534 --> 00:31:44.636
[phone clicking]

401
00:31:49.440 --> 00:31:50.841
[Man] Hello?

402
00:31:50.842 --> 00:31:52.342
- It's me.

403
00:31:52.343 --> 00:31:54.845
Yes. One of my patients
who's broken protocol.

404
00:31:54.846 --> 00:31:56.546
I need a wellness check.

405
00:31:56.547 --> 00:31:58.115
[Man] Which patient?

406
00:31:58.116 --> 00:31:59.616
- James Sunderland.

407
00:31:59.617 --> 00:32:01.018
[Man] Is he a danger
to himself or anyone?

408
00:32:01.019 --> 00:32:03.520
- I wouldn't say dangerous but...

409
00:32:03.521 --> 00:32:05.522
he's in trouble.

410
00:32:05.523 --> 00:32:08.525
[rain pattering]

411
00:32:08.526 --> 00:32:10.628
[metal clanks]

412
00:32:14.732 --> 00:32:16.134
[rain pattering]

413
00:32:18.903 --> 00:32:20.103
[door opens]

414
00:32:20.104 --> 00:32:21.539
[James panting]

415
00:32:30.648 --> 00:32:32.549
[wings flapping]

416
00:32:32.550 --> 00:32:34.052
[James groans]

417
00:32:36.955 --> 00:32:39.423
[James panting]

418
00:32:39.424 --> 00:32:41.125
[tense music]

419
00:33:05.049 --> 00:33:07.051
[door opens]

420
00:33:08.953 --> 00:33:11.322
-[keys thud]
-Mare?

421
00:33:14.058 --> 00:33:17.295
[distant chanting]

422
00:33:21.766 --> 00:33:24.669
- We understand completely
how you feel. [echoes]

423
00:33:28.206 --> 00:33:30.375
- Love is not an easy thing.
[echoes]

424
00:33:34.712 --> 00:33:36.947
- You can get your head
all twisted around.

425
00:33:36.948 --> 00:33:39.050
- You can lose
yourself in it. [echoes]

426
00:33:44.055 --> 00:33:46.290
- But we need to stay focused.

427
00:33:47.058 --> 00:33:48.326
[door creaks]

428
00:33:49.660 --> 00:33:53.698
- And here he is.
The man of the house.

429
00:33:55.366 --> 00:33:58.069
- What's going on. Jimmy boy?

430
00:33:58.936 --> 00:34:00.470
- What's going on here?

431
00:34:00.471 --> 00:34:02.072
[footsteps]

432
00:34:02.073 --> 00:34:03.674
[soft tense music]

433
00:34:15.319 --> 00:34:19.056
Okay. What the fuck was that?

434
00:34:19.057 --> 00:34:20.857
- I'm sorry.
They just showed up.

435
00:34:20.858 --> 00:34:21.858
- Wait. they just showed up?

436
00:34:21.859 --> 00:34:23.460
Twenty people just showed up?

437
00:34:23.461 --> 00:34:25.962
Again?
They're fucking weird. Mary.

438
00:34:25.963 --> 00:34:29.066
- They're my family. James.

439
00:34:29.067 --> 00:34:31.736
They took me in
after my father died.

440
00:34:35.173 --> 00:34:36.441
- All right.

441
00:34:40.378 --> 00:34:43.581
[uneasy music playing]

442
00:34:46.050 --> 00:34:47.718
Is that him?

443
00:34:50.121 --> 00:34:51.656
- [blowing]

444
00:34:55.927 --> 00:34:56.927
[closet door closes]

445
00:34:56.928 --> 00:34:58.162
[sighs]

446
00:35:01.165 --> 00:35:03.767
Please. James...

447
00:35:03.768 --> 00:35:05.469
Please.

448
00:35:05.470 --> 00:35:07.705
I want this to be
about you and me.

449
00:35:09.941 --> 00:35:11.175
Always.

450
00:35:12.176 --> 00:35:14.412
Always just us.

451
00:35:16.581 --> 00:35:19.584
[tense music]

452
00:35:20.785 --> 00:35:23.821
[wings flapping]

453
00:35:27.325 --> 00:35:28.693
[James sighs]

454
00:35:42.940 --> 00:35:45.775
- Brookhaven Hospital?

455
00:35:45.776 --> 00:35:47.311
[distant coughing]

456
00:35:48.579 --> 00:35:51.582
[gagging]

457
00:35:52.884 --> 00:35:54.285
[coughing]

458
00:36:00.057 --> 00:36:01.291
- What the fuck?

459
00:36:01.292 --> 00:36:02.292
- Are you okay?

460
00:36:02.293 --> 00:36:04.461
- It look like I'm okay?

461
00:36:04.462 --> 00:36:05.462
[breathing heavily]

462
00:36:05.463 --> 00:36:06.863
Who the hell are you?

463
00:36:06.864 --> 00:36:09.366
- I'm-I'm James. I'm...

464
00:36:09.367 --> 00:36:12.435
- Wait. why are you not sick
like everyone else?

465
00:36:12.436 --> 00:36:16.239
- What? No. I'm-I'm looking
for someone.

466
00:36:16.240 --> 00:36:17.240
[Eddie] Ain't nobody here.

467
00:36:17.241 --> 00:36:18.575
[James]
No. they're at the hospital.

468
00:36:18.576 --> 00:36:20.577
- [scoffs]

469
00:36:20.578 --> 00:36:22.879
[laughing]

470
00:36:22.880 --> 00:36:23.947
- What's funny?

471
00:36:23.948 --> 00:36:25.682
- Look around. buddy.

472
00:36:25.683 --> 00:36:27.851
Won't find anyone
at the hospital.

473
00:36:27.852 --> 00:36:30.188
City's one big cemetery.

474
00:36:32.089 --> 00:36:33.190
- Oh. God.
What is happening?

475
00:36:33.191 --> 00:36:35.058
- You should have seen it.

476
00:36:35.059 --> 00:36:38.161
No one could get their ass
in gear to react in time.

477
00:36:38.162 --> 00:36:39.396
Poor fucks.

478
00:36:39.397 --> 00:36:42.399
Whole town was rotten
before anyways. but this.

479
00:36:42.400 --> 00:36:44.367
this was something else.

480
00:36:44.368 --> 00:36:46.203
The fires...

481
00:36:46.204 --> 00:36:48.104
the water...

482
00:36:48.105 --> 00:36:50.173
everybody going insane.

483
00:36:50.174 --> 00:36:52.442
bleeding to death
out on the streets.

484
00:36:52.443 --> 00:36:54.344
All that crazy shit happened.

485
00:36:54.345 --> 00:36:56.146
and then these things
start to show up.

486
00:36:56.147 --> 00:36:58.482
[breathing hard]

487
00:37:00.084 --> 00:37:01.551
Wow.

488
00:37:01.552 --> 00:37:03.553
You've been lucky so far.

489
00:37:03.554 --> 00:37:04.589
- What?

490
00:37:05.957 --> 00:37:07.757
- Check this.

491
00:37:07.758 --> 00:37:08.892
- Jesus Christ.

492
00:37:08.893 --> 00:37:11.394
- [panting]

493
00:37:11.395 --> 00:37:14.764
So. what is it you do?

494
00:37:14.765 --> 00:37:15.966
- What do you mean.
what do I do?

495
00:37:15.967 --> 00:37:16.967
- In life. What do you do?

496
00:37:16.968 --> 00:37:18.001
- I'm a... I'm a painter.

497
00:37:18.002 --> 00:37:19.502
- A painter. huh?

498
00:37:19.503 --> 00:37:22.105
I ever heard of you?

499
00:37:22.106 --> 00:37:23.341
- I really don't know.

500
00:37:25.376 --> 00:37:28.311
- Always thought I had
the goods to be an artist.

501
00:37:28.312 --> 00:37:29.614
You ever have weird dreams?

502
00:37:32.583 --> 00:37:37.387
The shit that goes on in there.
you couldn't handle it.

503
00:37:37.388 --> 00:37:39.991
[baby screaming]

504
00:37:41.058 --> 00:37:42.192
[James] Do you hear that?

505
00:37:42.193 --> 00:37:43.560
- Hear what?

506
00:37:43.561 --> 00:37:45.195
- Sounds like a baby.

507
00:37:45.196 --> 00:37:46.496
- A baby?

508
00:37:46.497 --> 00:37:47.832
There ain't no baby here.

509
00:37:49.100 --> 00:37:51.401
[footsteps]

510
00:37:51.402 --> 00:37:53.738
- Can I ask a question?

511
00:37:54.605 --> 00:37:56.740
Why would you stay here?

512
00:37:56.741 --> 00:37:57.707
- You kidding?

513
00:37:57.708 --> 00:38:00.410
Place is rid of
all these assholes.

514
00:38:00.411 --> 00:38:02.012
It's heaven now.

515
00:38:02.013 --> 00:38:04.914
Got the entire city to myself.

516
00:38:04.915 --> 00:38:06.016
[distant baby cooing]

517
00:38:06.017 --> 00:38:07.485
- There...

518
00:38:10.221 --> 00:38:11.889
What the hell is this?

519
00:38:15.359 --> 00:38:16.559
Holy shit.

520
00:38:16.560 --> 00:38:18.461
- Uh-uh. be careful.

521
00:38:18.462 --> 00:38:20.464
- What are you talking about?
It's just a kid.

522
00:38:21.265 --> 00:38:24.968
Hey. what's your name?
I'm James.

523
00:38:24.969 --> 00:38:25.969
And this is...

524
00:38:25.970 --> 00:38:27.004
- Eddie.

525
00:38:28.873 --> 00:38:30.006
- I'm Laura.

526
00:38:30.007 --> 00:38:31.708
[James] Laura?

527
00:38:31.709 --> 00:38:33.877
Oh. you can't just stay in there
all by yourself. Laura.

528
00:38:33.878 --> 00:38:35.211
Come on. I think
you might be small enough

529
00:38:35.212 --> 00:38:36.680
to get through these bars.

530
00:38:36.681 --> 00:38:37.480
Come on.

531
00:38:37.481 --> 00:38:38.481
[Eddie] Let's get out of here.

532
00:38:38.482 --> 00:38:41.017
[James] Come on. it's okay.
You can trust me.

533
00:38:41.018 --> 00:38:42.519
You can trust me. Come on.

534
00:38:42.520 --> 00:38:44.387
- I'm telling you.
this is a bad idea.

535
00:38:44.388 --> 00:38:45.588
[James] Come on. Laura.

536
00:38:45.589 --> 00:38:47.458
I got you. Come on.
We can help you.

537
00:38:50.127 --> 00:38:51.629
[loud crackle. radio screeches]

538
00:38:53.331 --> 00:38:54.597
- We need to get
our asses outta here.

539
00:38:54.598 --> 00:38:55.699
- Come on. Laura.
It's all right.

540
00:38:55.700 --> 00:38:57.500
We're not gonna leave
without you. Come on.

541
00:38:57.501 --> 00:38:58.501
Just a bit closer.

542
00:38:58.502 --> 00:38:59.502
Come on. Laura.
-[distant growling]

543
00:38:59.503 --> 00:39:00.503
-Come on.
-[Laura gasps]

544
00:39:00.504 --> 00:39:02.472
[Eddie] Jimmy. let's go!

545
00:39:02.473 --> 00:39:04.008
[James groans]

546
00:39:04.975 --> 00:39:06.344
[metal scraping]

547
00:39:08.479 --> 00:39:09.913
- Would you look at that?

548
00:39:09.914 --> 00:39:13.183
You're all fucked up
like everyone else.

549
00:39:13.184 --> 00:39:14.719
[heavy footsteps]

550
00:39:15.920 --> 00:39:17.521
Get lost. kid!

551
00:39:18.889 --> 00:39:21.524
- Why would you do that.
