[whispers] Help.

829
01:00:47.677 --> 01:00:48.911
- Here. Let me see.

830
01:00:50.246 --> 01:00:51.279
[blood splatters]

831
01:00:51.280 --> 01:00:52.382
Oh. no.

832
01:00:53.583 --> 01:00:55.318
- [groans in pain]

833
01:01:00.790 --> 01:01:02.791
- [straining]

834
01:01:02.792 --> 01:01:04.694
[grunting]

835
01:01:08.231 --> 01:01:10.066
[Maria groaning]

836
01:01:17.273 --> 01:01:19.308
- [breathing heavily]

837
01:01:22.745 --> 01:01:23.980
[James groans]

838
01:01:34.457 --> 01:01:35.925
[doors squeak]

839
01:01:39.095 --> 01:01:42.098
[panting]

840
01:01:44.600 --> 01:01:47.704
- [gasps. groaning]

841
01:01:52.942 --> 01:01:55.177
You can say it.

842
01:01:55.178 --> 01:01:56.946
- What?

843
01:01:57.780 --> 01:01:59.382
- I look just like her.

844
01:02:01.884 --> 01:02:05.087
- No. No. no. no.
How would you know that?

845
01:02:05.088 --> 01:02:07.756
- It's how you look at me.

846
01:02:07.757 --> 01:02:10.058
- [breathing deeply]

847
01:02:10.059 --> 01:02:14.763
Look. I'm gonna go upstairs.
I want you to stay here.

848
01:02:14.764 --> 01:02:15.897
- [grunts] No. don't leave me.

849
01:02:15.898 --> 01:02:16.998
- You'll be safer here.

850
01:02:16.999 --> 01:02:19.401
I'm gonna look for Mary.
and I'll come right back.

851
01:02:19.402 --> 01:02:21.703
- Promise me something.

852
01:02:21.704 --> 01:02:24.506
If you find out she's gone.
we leave.

853
01:02:24.507 --> 01:02:25.807
Together.

854
01:02:25.808 --> 01:02:27.410
We don't look back.

855
01:02:34.784 --> 01:02:36.385
- [strains with effort]

856
01:02:41.758 --> 01:02:43.192
[Laura] Who is she?

857
01:02:47.797 --> 01:02:49.499
- Just someone
I'm trying to help.

858
01:02:51.968 --> 01:02:58.106
Now. Laura. you have to
tell me where Mary is.

859
01:02:58.107 --> 01:02:59.908
- Doesn't look like
you want to find her.

860
01:02:59.909 --> 01:03:03.712
- No. I do.
It's all I want.

861
01:03:03.713 --> 01:03:07.015
Now. please. where is she?

862
01:03:07.016 --> 01:03:08.517
- My baby's sad!

863
01:03:08.518 --> 01:03:11.521
[doll bawling]

864
01:03:17.393 --> 01:03:20.529
He's cold and sad.

865
01:03:20.530 --> 01:03:23.298
Sad because nobody loved him.

866
01:03:23.299 --> 01:03:25.300
Just like Mary.

867
01:03:25.301 --> 01:03:27.068
- What?

868
01:03:27.069 --> 01:03:31.007
- You left her all
[shrieks] alone!

869
01:03:33.109 --> 01:03:35.010
- Ah!

870
01:03:35.011 --> 01:03:37.814
- You have to get to her
before it's too late.

871
01:03:41.984 --> 01:03:44.120
- No. wait! Laura!

872
01:03:45.521 --> 01:03:46.522
Laura!

873
01:03:50.026 --> 01:03:53.262
[footsteps thudding on stairs]

874
01:04:05.808 --> 01:04:08.009
Why are you doing this?

875
01:04:08.010 --> 01:04:09.879
- No one said it would be easy.

876
01:04:10.913 --> 01:04:14.016
[door opens. squeaks]

877
01:04:18.487 --> 01:04:20.822
- [panting]

878
01:04:20.823 --> 01:04:22.358
No.

879
01:04:25.127 --> 01:04:27.029
[door opens. squeaks]

880
01:04:28.331 --> 01:04:30.432
What?

881
01:04:30.433 --> 01:04:31.968
Laura?

882
01:04:34.303 --> 01:04:35.237
- [giggles]

883
01:04:35.238 --> 01:04:37.373
-Laura?!
-[door closes]

884
01:04:38.407 --> 01:04:39.507
- Laura?!

885
01:04:39.508 --> 01:04:41.210
Laura. open the door!

886
01:04:42.912 --> 01:04:45.714
-[banging on door]
-Open the door!

887
01:04:45.715 --> 01:04:49.018
[strange growls]

888
01:05:12.642 --> 01:05:13.642
[loud shrieks]

889
01:05:13.643 --> 01:05:15.378
[hospital bed sliding]

890
01:05:23.386 --> 01:05:26.389
[bed clanking]

891
01:05:29.191 --> 01:05:30.993
[Laura]
Why'd you come. James?

892
01:05:35.998 --> 01:05:38.134
What did you think you'd find?

893
01:05:55.151 --> 01:05:56.686
[blood drips]

894
01:05:58.020 --> 01:05:59.255
[James] Mary.

895
01:06:15.571 --> 01:06:16.538
[pipe clanks to floor]

896
01:06:16.539 --> 01:06:20.508
[James choking]

897
01:06:20.509 --> 01:06:24.045
[Laura] Come back
when you're ready. James.

898
01:06:24.046 --> 01:06:26.548
-[choking]
-[Doctor] Mr. Sunderland?

899
01:06:26.549 --> 01:06:28.450
Mr. Sunderland?

900
01:06:28.451 --> 01:06:30.352
Are you with us. Mr. Sunderland?

901
01:06:30.353 --> 01:06:32.420
[heart monitor beeping]

902
01:06:32.421 --> 01:06:33.855
- What?

903
01:06:33.856 --> 01:06:36.858
What's going on?
Where am I?

904
01:06:36.859 --> 01:06:38.159
Where am I?

905
01:06:38.160 --> 01:06:39.561
- Brookhaven Hospital.

906
01:06:39.562 --> 01:06:41.030
Silent Hill.

907
01:06:42.031 --> 01:06:44.132
- Where is she?

908
01:06:44.133 --> 01:06:45.533
Where is she?

909
01:06:45.534 --> 01:06:46.534
- Where is who?

910
01:06:46.535 --> 01:06:48.003
- Mary. Mary Crane.

911
01:06:48.004 --> 01:06:49.705
[footsteps approaching]

912
01:06:51.440 --> 01:06:52.441
What?

913
01:06:56.479 --> 01:06:58.646
- Hello. James.

914
01:06:58.647 --> 01:07:02.418
- I know where she is.
[breathes heavily]

915
01:07:04.453 --> 01:07:07.555
- You need to let go of her.

916
01:07:07.556 --> 01:07:09.025
She's gone.

917
01:07:10.760 --> 01:07:13.029
She's dead. James.

918
01:07:15.331 --> 01:07:18.066
She's been dead for months now.

919
01:07:18.067 --> 01:07:20.069
You know that.

920
01:07:24.340 --> 01:07:27.142
- Why would you say that?

921
01:07:27.143 --> 01:07:30.211
[eerie ambient music]

922
01:07:30.212 --> 01:07:32.148
[M] We've got a lot
of serious work to do.

923
01:07:33.149 --> 01:07:34.683
But we'll get you through it.

924
01:07:36.052 --> 01:07:38.454
You just have to
promise me something.

925
01:07:41.657 --> 01:07:43.658
You need to want to
see yourself get better

926
01:07:43.659 --> 01:07:45.461
as much as I do.

927
01:07:58.874 --> 01:08:02.078
[emotional music playing]

928
01:08:07.349 --> 01:08:10.553
[car approaching]

929
01:08:31.273 --> 01:08:32.708
[door opens]

930
01:08:39.682 --> 01:08:42.118
[Mary] Why are you
sitting in the dark?

931
01:08:43.385 --> 01:08:45.053
[suitcase slides]

932
01:08:45.054 --> 01:08:46.921
- Pack your things.

933
01:08:46.922 --> 01:08:49.357
I want us out of here.

934
01:08:49.358 --> 01:08:51.560
- Why are you acting like this?

935
01:08:53.028 --> 01:08:54.864
- Guess what I did today.

936
01:08:56.565 --> 01:08:59.168
I saw this girl
across the street...

937
01:09:01.070 --> 01:09:02.737
so I followed her.

938
01:09:02.738 --> 01:09:04.139
[Mary] Stop.

939
01:09:04.140 --> 01:09:06.574
- I went down this long
flight of stairs.

940
01:09:06.575 --> 01:09:07.976
[Mary] Stop.

941
01:09:07.977 --> 01:09:10.812
- And I saw these monsters.

942
01:09:10.813 --> 01:09:12.480
I saw them tear her apart.

943
01:09:12.481 --> 01:09:15.284
-Just stop!
-[glass shatters]

944
01:09:19.688 --> 01:09:21.723
- How long?

945
01:09:21.724 --> 01:09:23.425
- Since I was a girl.

946
01:09:25.461 --> 01:09:28.730
- Why would your father
do this to you?

947
01:09:28.731 --> 01:09:29.832
- I don't know.

948
01:09:31.367 --> 01:09:33.169
I never had a choice.

949
01:09:35.371 --> 01:09:37.439
- This is your last chance.

950
01:09:38.941 --> 01:09:41.276
Walk out that door with me now.

951
01:09:41.277 --> 01:09:42.377
- Not when you're like this.

952
01:09:42.378 --> 01:09:44.779
- What am I like?

953
01:09:44.780 --> 01:09:46.781
- Scared.

954
01:09:46.782 --> 01:09:48.583
- You think I'm scared?

955
01:09:48.584 --> 01:09:50.652
[raises voice]
I am not scared!

956
01:09:50.653 --> 01:09:53.388
I am not scared of any of you.

957
01:09:53.389 --> 01:09:55.890
[Mary whimpers]

958
01:09:55.891 --> 01:09:58.293
- But you're disgusted.

959
01:09:58.294 --> 01:10:00.361
Say it.

960
01:10:00.362 --> 01:10:02.831
Say I'm disgusting to you.
Say it!

961
01:10:05.067 --> 01:10:09.103
That day. I was leaving.

962
01:10:09.104 --> 01:10:11.674
I was leaving.
and then you showed up.

963
01:10:14.476 --> 01:10:17.178
- Why-why didn't you
just tell me?

964
01:10:17.179 --> 01:10:19.481
- Because I knew you'd walk away.

965
01:10:21.483 --> 01:10:24.185
I see the way
you're looking at me.

966
01:10:24.186 --> 01:10:26.788
That'll never change now.

967
01:10:26.789 --> 01:10:31.492
I told you there were things.
You-you promised me.

968
01:10:31.493 --> 01:10:34.730
[emotional music]

969
01:10:39.501 --> 01:10:41.870
[footsteps receding]

970
01:10:52.481 --> 01:10:53.983
[car alarm beeps]

971
01:10:57.052 --> 01:10:58.587
[car door opens]

972
01:11:20.409 --> 01:11:21.610
[car door shuts]

973
01:11:27.216 --> 01:11:29.317
[Doctor] How is he today?

974
01:11:29.318 --> 01:11:30.919
[M] Calm. I guess.

975
01:11:31.987 --> 01:11:36.391
I've worked with vets.
all kinds of trauma.

976
01:11:36.392 --> 01:11:40.295
but this is different.
He won't let me in at all.

977
01:11:40.296 --> 01:11:42.196
- How long have you been
treating him?

978
01:11:42.197 --> 01:11:44.333
- Almost a year.

979
01:11:45.301 --> 01:11:47.402
But it's gotten worse.

980
01:11:47.403 --> 01:11:52.307
That woman. Mary.
she was everything to him.

981
01:11:52.308 --> 01:11:53.408
Since her lost her.

982
01:11:53.409 --> 01:11:56.077
it's like he lost
his grip on reality.

983
01:11:56.078 --> 01:11:58.747
and his desire to regain it.

984
01:12:01.050 --> 01:12:03.519
Mary died after their breakup.

985
01:12:04.586 --> 01:12:06.888
And he just won't accept it.

986
01:12:06.889 --> 01:12:09.691
[birds chirping]

987
01:12:09.692 --> 01:12:12.895
[emotional music playing]

988
01:12:16.098 --> 01:12:18.434
It's good to see you up. James.

989
01:12:19.501 --> 01:12:21.837
How are you feeling today?

990
01:12:24.673 --> 01:12:26.008
James?

991
01:12:30.512 --> 01:12:32.614
- I just wish...

992
01:12:33.782 --> 01:12:36.452
I wish I hadn't let her down.

993
01:12:39.788 --> 01:12:42.358
- You're blaming yourself. but...

994
01:12:43.792 --> 01:12:47.128
all this chaos in your mind...

995
01:12:47.129 --> 01:12:50.431
it's not real.

996
01:12:50.432 --> 01:12:56.337
It’s not real.
and it almost destroyed you.

997
01:12:56.338 --> 01:12:58.506
We can still fix this.

998
01:12:58.507 --> 01:13:01.377
But it's got to be
your decision.

999
01:13:05.681 --> 01:13:09.852
- Thank you.
For everything.

1000
01:13:14.189 --> 01:13:17.393
[footsteps receding]

1001
01:13:29.171 --> 01:13:32.408
[tense. sinister music playing]

1002
01:13:37.212 --> 01:13:40.515
[wings flapping]

1003
01:13:40.516 --> 01:13:43.752
[emergency alarm blaring]

1004
01:13:52.227 --> 01:13:55.464
[walls crackling]

1005
01:14:04.840 --> 01:14:06.942
[Maria] You didn't find her?

1006
01:14:11.713 --> 01:14:15.651
Then we can leave.
Together.

1007
01:14:17.453 --> 01:14:19.520
[groans]

1008
01:14:19.521 --> 01:14:22.524
You promised. James.

1009
01:14:25.294 --> 01:14:28.497
[emotional music playing]

1010
01:14:29.431 --> 01:14:31.934
- You look just like her.

1011
01:14:33.836 --> 01:14:36.472
- I never told you my name.

1012
01:14:40.142 --> 01:14:41.643
It's Maria.

1013
01:14:45.447 --> 01:14:48.650
[kissing]

1014
01:14:55.524 --> 01:14:58.259
Or we can stay here together...

1015
01:14:58.260 --> 01:15:00.528
if you want.

1016
01:15:00.529 --> 01:15:02.164
Just us.

1017
01:15:09.204 --> 01:15:10.539
What is it?

1018
01:15:12.508 --> 01:15:15.443
Where are you going?

1019
01:15:15.444 --> 01:15:17.179
[breathing heavily]

1020
01:15:20.449 --> 01:15:22.049
James.

1021
01:15:22.050 --> 01:15:23.519
Wait for me.

1022
01:15:24.953 --> 01:15:26.889
You won't find her down there.

1023
01:15:29.057 --> 01:15:30.659
[elevator clanks]

1024
01:15:31.560 --> 01:15:33.195
[elevator pings]

1025
01:15:35.531 --> 01:15:36.932
Please.

1026
01:15:42.638 --> 01:15:45.874
[elevator door closing]

1027
01:15:49.611 --> 01:15:51.280
[elevator pings]

1028
01:15:52.247 --> 01:15:54.649
[elevator in free fall]

1029
01:15:54.650 --> 01:15:56.551
Why are you doing this?

1030
01:15:56.552 --> 01:15:58.787
[tense music playing]

1031
01:16:02.057 --> 01:16:04.159
You were free of all this pain.

1032
01:16:09.364 --> 01:16:10.899
James!

1033
01:16:17.039 --> 01:16:18.206
James!

1034
01:16:19.441 --> 01:16:20.676
James!

1035
01:16:22.377 --> 01:16:23.477
James!

1036
01:16:23.478 --> 01:16:25.280
[elevator powering down]

1037
01:16:30.352 --> 01:16:31.954
[elevator door opening]

1038
01:16:34.556 --> 01:16:36.158
You can't go in there.

1039
01:16:54.643 --> 01:16:55.944
Let's go back.

1040
01:16:57.879 --> 01:16:59.815
We can still go back.

1041
01:17:03.852 --> 01:17:06.188
Please don't go any further.

1042
01:17:24.473 --> 01:17:26.908
It's over if you want it to be.

1043
01:17:32.581 --> 01:17:34.683
- Mary's not dead.

1044
01:17:36.084 --> 01:17:37.319
Not to me.

1045
01:17:39.287 --> 01:17:40.822
And you're not real.

1046
01:17:42.391 --> 01:17:44.492
You're just in my way.

1047
01:17:44.493 --> 01:17:45.760
- No.

1048
01:17:45.761 --> 01:17:47.928
No. no.
No. no. no. no. no.

1049
01:17:47.929 --> 01:17:49.665
Look at me. James.

1050
01:17:52.267 --> 01:17:54.068
- Goodbye. Maria.

1051
01:17:54.069 --> 01:17:56.071
[lights flickering. clanking]

1052
01:17:58.373 --> 01:18:00.676
- [screams in pain]

1053
01:18:02.477 --> 01:18:04.780
[wet squelching]

1054
01:18:08.684 --> 01:18:10.686
[blood spurting]

1055
01:18:35.644 --> 01:18:38.914
[rhythmic heavy clanking]

1056
01:18:58.366 --> 01:18:59.367
[bottle clanks]

1057
01:19:10.212 --> 01:19:11.480
[James groans]

1058
01:19:13.181 --> 01:19:16.384
[water splashes.
blooping softly]

1059
01:19:36.004 --> 01:19:39.241
- [gasping for air]

1060
01:19:42.677 --> 01:19:44.513
[breathing heavily]

1061
01:19:49.384 --> 01:19:52.354
[flames roaring]

1062
01:20:08.503 --> 01:20:11.506
[roaring fire]

1063
01:20:14.709 --> 01:20:17.946
[flames roaring]

1064
01:20:19.915 --> 01:20:21.416
[distant thud]

1065
01:20:30.692 --> 01:20:32.260
[Laura] You're finally here.

1066
01:20:34.262 --> 01:20:35.362
- Laura?

1067
01:20:35.363 --> 01:20:36.364
[Laura giggles]

1068
01:20:38.867 --> 01:20:42.236
[soft music playing]

1069
01:20:42.237 --> 01:20:44.272
[giggles]

1070
01:20:46.474 --> 01:20:48.944
[James] I'm not playing
anymore. Laura.

1071
01:20:50.745 --> 01:20:52.848
- Do you think
you're ready to face it?

1072
01:20:57.385 --> 01:21:00.521
Do you think
you're ready to face us?

1073
01:21:00.522 --> 01:21:01.523
- [shuddering]

1074
01:21:05.594 --> 01:21:07.863
[doll cooing]

1075
01:21:12.834 --> 01:21:15.135
[James] Why are you
doing this to me?

1076
01:21:15.136 --> 01:21:17.105
- To help you remember.

1077
01:21:18.874 --> 01:21:20.674
What's her name?

1078
01:21:20.675 --> 01:21:21.976
- What?

1079
01:21:21.977 --> 01:21:23.010
- Think. James.

1080
01:21:23.011 --> 01:21:24.346
- [groans]

1081
01:21:26.548 --> 01:21:28.250
- What's Mary's full name?

1082
01:21:30.719 --> 01:21:32.519
- [groans]

1083
01:21:32.520 --> 01:21:34.356
- Our full name. James...

1084
01:21:35.590 --> 01:21:37.225
- [groans]

1085
01:21:42.530 --> 01:21:45.099
[breathing heavily]

1086
01:21:45.100 --> 01:21:46.902
[Laura] It's time now.

1087
01:21:48.703 --> 01:21:50.538
[flames crackling]

1088
01:21:53.108 --> 01:21:56.544
And now.
there's nothing left to hide.

1089
01:21:58.780 --> 01:22:00.348
[flames crackling]

1090
01:22:08.590 --> 01:22:09.723
[door closes]

1091
01:22:09.724 --> 01:22:11.926
[eerie ambient music]

1092
01:22:11.927 --> 01:22:14.262
[Angela sobbing]

1093
01:22:22.837 --> 01:22:25.039
- Haven't you had enough?

1094
01:22:25.040 --> 01:22:26.540
Disgusting.

1095
01:22:26.541 --> 01:22:27.676
You're disgusting!

1096
01:22:30.912 --> 01:22:33.147
You... you see.

1097
01:22:33.148 --> 01:22:35.250
Please tell me you can see it.

1098
01:22:38.353 --> 01:22:40.821
I can't get away from him.

1099
01:22:40.822 --> 01:22:43.959
He'll never stop hurting me.

1100
01:22:45.126 --> 01:22:46.927
- Let me help you.

1101
01:22:46.928 --> 01:22:48.595
- Don't! Don't.

1102
01:22:48.596 --> 01:22:49.897
Stay away.

1103
01:22:49.898 --> 01:22:52.033
[sobbing]

1104
01:22:53.401 --> 01:22:54.536
- Please.

1105
01:22:58.506 --> 01:22:59.674
[grunts]

1106
01:23:18.560 --> 01:23:20.662
[growling softly]

1107
01:23:30.038 --> 01:23:32.374
[James breathing heavily]

1108
01:23:38.146 --> 01:23:40.248
[tense music]

1109
01:23:41.950 --> 01:23:43.685
[growling softy]

1110
01:23:45.820 --> 01:23:46.954
[James] Mary?

1111
01:23:46.955 --> 01:23:48.456
[growling]

1112
01:24:09.644 --> 01:24:10.779
[whispers] I'm sorry.

1113
01:24:12.047 --> 01:24:13.314
[squeals]

1114
01:24:28.163 --> 01:24:31.399
-[door opens]
-[fire roaring]

1115
01:24:38.673 --> 01:24:40.275
Mary?!

1116
01:24:43.978 --> 01:24:45.345
No. wait!

1117
01:24:45.346 --> 01:24:47.082
[running footsteps]

1118
01:24:49.851 --> 01:24:51.152
[door opens]

1119
01:24:59.127 --> 01:25:02.330
[fire crackling]

1120
01:25:31.259 --> 01:25:34.462
[music playing on radio]

1121
01:25:41.169 --> 01:25:43.304
[M] You need to let go of her.

1122
01:25:45.573 --> 01:25:46.875
She's gone.

1123
01:25:48.776 --> 01:25:50.712
She's dead. James.

1124
01:25:53.281 --> 01:25:55.983
She's been dead for months now.

1125
01:25:55.984 --> 01:25:57.719
You know that.

1126
01:26:04.392 --> 01:26:06.761
[birds chirping]

1127
01:26:23.178 --> 01:26:24.945
[Mary] You came.

1128
01:26:24.946 --> 01:26:26.314
- Of course.

1129
01:26:28.082 --> 01:26:29.283
As soon as I could.

1130
01:26:29.284 --> 01:26:31.451
[Mary] It's okay.

1131
01:26:31.452 --> 01:26:33.453
- I never should have left.

1132
01:26:33.454 --> 01:26:36.190
[Mary] Whether you would've
stayed or not.

1133
01:26:36.191 --> 01:26:38.792
I still would've gotten sick.

1134
01:26:38.793 --> 01:26:41.094
[James] Well. maybe
I could've helped.

1135
01:26:41.095 --> 01:26:42.830
- No one could've.

1136
01:26:44.065 --> 01:26:46.467
My father poisoned me.

1137
01:26:47.602 --> 01:26:50.205
He poisoned me my whole life.

1138
01:26:53.641 --> 01:26:56.277
I tried to shield you from it.

1139
01:26:57.178 --> 01:26:58.880
- I know.

1140
01:27:00.682 --> 01:27:03.284
[Mary] Can you help me lie down?

1141
01:27:08.256 --> 01:27:09.690
[James] Sure.

1142
01:27:09.691 --> 01:27:12.894
[emotional music
playing on radio]

1143
01:27:26.374 --> 01:27:29.744
- Okay.
Okay. okay. okay.

1144
01:27:31.646 --> 01:27:32.880
- [groans]

1145
01:27:42.290 --> 01:27:43.491
- [silent sobs]

1146
01:27:49.731 --> 01:27:50.898
[glass breaks]

1147
01:27:52.967 --> 01:27:54.801
Come on.

1148
01:27:54.802 --> 01:27:56.803
There you go.

1149
01:27:56.804 --> 01:27:58.473
All right.

1150
01:28:04.178 --> 01:28:06.347
Just tell me how I can help you.

1151
01:28:07.815 --> 01:28:09.416
- You know.

1152
01:28:09.417 --> 01:28:10.918
- [sniffles]

1153
01:28:12.220 --> 01:28:15.290
- He's lived inside of me
for so long.

1154
01:28:16.291 --> 01:28:18.959
I don't want him there anymore.

1155
01:28:18.960 --> 01:28:20.060
- I can't do that.

1156
01:28:20.061 --> 01:28:21.596
- I want to be free.

1157
01:28:24.499 --> 01:28:26.467
Please. James.

1158
01:28:27.669 --> 01:28:29.003
Please.

1159
01:28:32.874 --> 01:28:34.808
Help me now.

1160
01:28:34.809 --> 01:28:36.444
- [James sobbing]

1161
01:28:38.212 --> 01:28:40.448
[emotional music
playing on radio]

1162
01:28:51.726 --> 01:28:53.494
[crying]

1163
01:29:27.862 --> 01:29:29.630
[wings flapping]

1164
01:29:42.276 --> 01:29:44.712
[ground crumbling]

1165
01:30:00.128 --> 01:30:03.398
[ethereal music playing]

1166
01:30:27.622 --> 01:30:29.524
[ground crumbling]

1167
01:30:33.728 --> 01:30:37.632
[emotional music playing]

1168
01:30:50.611 --> 01:30:53.815
[wings flapping]

1169
01:31:08.596 --> 01:31:12.499
That day. I should've
died with you.

1170
01:31:12.500 --> 01:31:15.770
[wings flapping]

1171
01:31:32.053 --> 01:31:33.221
You forgave me.

1172
01:31:34.822 --> 01:31:37.558
but I could never
forgive myself.

1173
01:31:45.199 --> 01:31:47.768
I was so selfish. Mare.

1174
01:31:53.241 --> 01:31:55.176
Selfish and scared.

1175
01:32:15.463 --> 01:32:17.832
[car engine revving]

1176
01:32:21.068 --> 01:32:22.737
[water splashes]

1177
01:32:41.522 --> 01:32:43.190
I'm ready now.

1178
01:32:47.662 --> 01:32:49.564
No matter what it takes.

1179
01:32:51.832 --> 01:32:53.968
No matter where it takes us.

1180
01:32:59.674 --> 01:33:00.975
This time...

1181
01:33:04.245 --> 01:33:06.047
I won't let go.

1182
01:33:19.427 --> 01:33:22.262
[Doctor]
Mr. Sunderland?

1183
01:33:22.263 --> 01:33:23.563
Mr. Sunderland?

1184
01:33:23.564 --> 01:33:25.132
[truck honking]

1185
01:33:26.067 --> 01:33:28.235
[Doctor]
Are you with us. Mr. Sunderland?

1186
01:33:29.236 --> 01:33:30.270
[truck honking]

1187
01:33:30.271 --> 01:33:35.943
[tire screeching]

1188
01:33:38.446 --> 01:33:40.214
[breathing heavily] What?

1189
01:33:42.883 --> 01:33:44.184
[Mary] Oh. come on.

1190
01:33:44.185 --> 01:33:46.853
[running footsteps]

1191
01:33:46.854 --> 01:33:48.355
You've got to be kidding me.

1192
01:33:48.356 --> 01:33:51.359
[emotional music]

1193
01:33:55.763 --> 01:33:57.665
- I'm so sorry.

1194
01:33:59.367 --> 01:34:00.567
Are you okay?

1195
01:34:00.568 --> 01:34:02.069
- Yeah.
No. I'm fine. I'm fine.

1196
01:34:08.476 --> 01:34:10.077
Are you okay?

1197
01:34:11.145 --> 01:34:12.380
- I think so.

1198
01:34:22.657 --> 01:34:23.991
It's okay. I got it.

1199
01:34:26.861 --> 01:34:28.361
The latch is broken.

1200
01:34:28.362 --> 01:34:29.362
- How do you know that?

1201
01:34:29.363 --> 01:34:31.966
[distant honking]

1202
01:34:33.467 --> 01:34:34.969
Shoot. that's my bus.

1203
01:34:36.270 --> 01:34:37.938
Hey. wait!

1204
01:34:41.876 --> 01:34:43.677
[suitcase latch snaps]

1205
01:34:43.678 --> 01:34:45.578
[horn honks]

1206
01:34:45.579 --> 01:34:47.747
Sorry. just...

1207
01:34:47.748 --> 01:34:49.684
[bus engine revs]

1208
01:34:51.686 --> 01:34:53.787
- Where were you heading?

1209
01:34:53.788 --> 01:34:55.422
- The next city.

1210
01:34:55.423 --> 01:34:58.692
- Well. I just ruined your day.

1211
01:34:58.693 --> 01:35:02.262
Wouldn't be much of a gentleman
if I didn't try and help fix it.

1212
01:35:02.263 --> 01:35:03.697
- A gentleman?

1213
01:35:03.698 --> 01:35:05.765
Didn't know
they made those anymore.

1214
01:35:05.766 --> 01:35:07.801
- Gentleman named James.

1215
01:35:07.802 --> 01:35:10.370
-I'm...
-Mary.

1216
01:35:10.371 --> 01:35:12.073
I saw it on your case.

1217
01:35:13.541 --> 01:35:15.076
- [chuckles]

1218
01:35:17.478 --> 01:35:19.080
[car hood shuts]

1219
01:35:22.383 --> 01:35:24.719
[wind blows]

1220
01:35:26.287 --> 01:35:29.189
You're a painter?

1221
01:35:29.190 --> 01:35:30.391
- Yeah.

1222
01:35:33.494 --> 01:35:34.829
[car door closes]

1223
01:35:41.569 --> 01:35:43.237
- What do you paint?

1224
01:35:49.510 --> 01:35:52.779
[car engine starts. revving]

1225
01:35:52.780 --> 01:35:55.983
[funky music playing]

1226
01:35:58.686 --> 01:36:00.354
[car tires screech]

1227
01:36:37.358 --> 01:36:40.361
[static noise]

1228
01:36:46.367 --> 01:36:49.837
["Letter - from the Lost
Days" by Akira Yamaoka]

1229
01:37:15.196 --> 01:37:19.165
♪ A letter to my future self

1230
01:37:19.166 --> 01:37:22.702
♪ Am I still happy? I began

1231
01:37:22.703 --> 01:37:26.206
♪ Have I grown more pretty

1232
01:37:26.207 --> 01:37:30.176
♪ Is Daddy still a good man?

1233
01:37:30.177 --> 01:37:33.413
♪ Am I still friends
With Colleen ♪

1234
01:37:33.414 --> 01:37:37.817
♪ I'm sure that
I'm still laughing ♪

1235
01:37:37.818 --> 01:37:43.390
♪ Aren't I?

1236
01:37:51.832 --> 01:37:55.335
♪ Hey there to my future self

1237
01:37:55.336 --> 01:37:59.172
♪ If you forget how to smile

1238
01:37:59.173 --> 01:38:02.609
♪ I have this to tell you

1239
01:38:02.610 --> 01:38:06.212
♪ Remember it once in a while

1240
01:38:06.213 --> 01:38:10.116
♪ Ten years ago
Your past self ♪

1241
01:38:10.117 --> 01:38:13.686
♪ Prayed for your happiness

1242
01:38:13.687 --> 01:38:20.827
♪ Please don't lose hope

1243
01:38:20.828 --> 01:38:27.800
♪ Oh oh what a pair
Me and you ♪

1244
01:38:27.801 --> 01:38:35.208
♪ Put here to feel joy
Not be blue ♪

1245
01:38:35.209 --> 01:38:42.582
♪ Sad times and bad times
See them through ♪

1246
01:38:42.583 --> 01:38:49.622
♪ Soon we will know
If it's for real ♪

1247
01:38:49.623 --> 01:38:57.196
♪ What we both feel

1248
01:38:57.197 --> 01:38:59.132
♪ Though I can't know for sure

1249
01:38:59.133 --> 01:39:01.268
♪ How things worked out for us

1250
01:39:02.836 --> 01:39:04.704
♪ So be happy

1251
01:39:04.705 --> 01:39:06.706
♪ For me

1252
01:39:06.707 --> 01:39:09.142
♪ For you

1253
01:39:09.143 --> 01:39:13.447
♪ Feel joy ♪

1254
01:39:14.248 --> 01:39:17.418
[mellow music playing]
